						               													<description>(from Histoire &amp;amp; Collections webpage:)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;en fran&amp;ccedil;ais:&amp;#10;R&amp;egrave;gle compl&amp;egrave;te pour le jeu avec figurines de 6 &amp;agrave; 25 mm, pour la p&amp;eacute;riode 1792-1815. De Bonaparte &amp;agrave; Napol&amp;eacute;on &amp;mdash; ou DBN &amp;mdash; s&amp;rsquo;est affirm&amp;eacute;e comme la nouvelle r&amp;egrave;gle de r&amp;eacute;f&amp;eacute;rence sur cette p&amp;eacute;riode &amp;eacute;pique. La premi&amp;egrave;re &amp;eacute;dition, rapidement &amp;eacute;puis&amp;eacute;e, se trouve &amp;agrave; pr&amp;eacute;sent remani&amp;eacute;e et am&amp;eacute;lior&amp;eacute;e gr&amp;acirc;ce &amp;agrave; l&amp;rsquo;exp&amp;eacute;rience des tr&amp;egrave;s nombreux joueurs pratiquant DBN. Cette seconde &amp;eacute;dition, d&amp;eacute;sormais indispensable &amp;agrave; tous, comprend les r&amp;egrave;gles compl&amp;egrave;tes amend&amp;eacute;es et des marqueurs sur planche cartonn&amp;eacute;e &amp;agrave; d&amp;eacute;couper.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(BGG user translation and description:)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In English:&amp;#10;Complete rules for 6 to 25mm miniatures games, 1792-1815 period. De Bonaparte &amp;agrave; Napol&amp;eacute;on &amp;mdash; or DBN &amp;mdash; has now became the new reference rule on this epic period. The first edition, quickly sold out, is now revised and improved thanks to the experience of many players practicing DBN. This second edition now indispensable to all, includes the complete rules amended and markers on cardboard sheets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These rules are based in the DBX system (DBM, DBA, DBR, HOTT) but applied for the Revolutionary and the Napoleonic Wars into  army corps level. They cover the maneuvres, formations and combat of the period in a way which would be very familiar to those players of the before mentioned games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;IN FRENCH ONLY.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
